org.rocksdb

Class RocksCallbackObject

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.rocksdb.AbstractNativeReference
      • org.rocksdb.AbstractImmutableNativeReference
        • org.rocksdb.RocksCallbackObject
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.AutoCloseable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractCompactionFilterFactory, AbstractComparator, AbstractTransactionNotifier, Logger, WriteBatch.Handler

    public abstract class RocksCallbackObject
extends AbstractImmutableNativeReference
    RocksCallbackObject is similar to RocksObject but varies in its construction as it is designed for Java objects which have functions which are called from C++ via JNI. RocksCallbackObject is the base-class any RocksDB classes that acts as a callback from some underlying underlying native C++ rocksdb object. The use of RocksObject should always be preferred over RocksCallbackObject if callbacks are not required.
